<TITLE> Lawyer shot dead in Pirojpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pirojpur, Oct 11 (bdnews24.com)Unnamed gunmen shot and killed a lawyer at Kaukhali in Pirojpur at around midday on Sunday. Gias Uddin Khan Masud, 35, a member of Pirojpur District Lawyers' Association, was from Sangol village under Swarupkathi Upazila. Masud rode a rickshaw after withdrawing money from the Kaukhali branch of Sonali Bank. The criminals shot him on the left side of the head when he reached in front of the Kochuakathi bailey bridge and took the money, Mohammed Shahidullah Chowdhury, superintendent of police of Pirojpur, told bdnews24.com. The locals first took him to Kaukhali health complex. Later, he was sent to the Sher-e-Bangla Medical College in Barisal where the on-duty doctor declared him dead at 2 pm. The body is at the morgue of the hospital for autopsy. bdne
